Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 24 November 2024

Introduction
At twodo.it, your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information while using our app.

Information We Collect

- Personal Information: May include data you provide voluntarily, such as your name or email address.
- Usage Data: Includes information about app interactions, device identifiers, and error logs.
- Third-Party Services: Data may be collected by integrated services (e.g., analytics providers) under their policies.

How We Use Your Information

- To operate and enhance app features.
- To send essential updates or notifications.
- For analytics and app improvement purposes.

Data Sharing
We do not sell or share user data except as follows:

- Service Providers: For analytics or technical support.
- Legal Compliance: If required by applicable laws or regulations.

Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

- Access or correct your personal data.
- Request deletion of your data.
- Limit or withdraw consent for data processing.

Data Security
We employ industry-standard measures to secure your data. However, no system is completely secure.

Policy Updates
This policy may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the app signifies agreement to the updated terms.
